[6] Canada (Calgary)
Date: 3 Apr 2014
Source: Huffington Post Canada [edited]
http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2014/04/03/measles-edmonton_n_5086660.html


Edmonton is now reporting a case of measles in its region, a day after Calgary confirmed 2 further cases in the city, bringing the total number of cases for the contagious virus in the province to 6. According to Global News, Alberta Health Services confirmed the cases today [3 Apr 2014], noting public locations from 25-26 Mar 2014 where people may have been exposed to the virus.

Measles, which is spread through direct contact or airborne secretions from an infected person, has been reported in various parts of Canada throughout the beginning of 2014, including a case of 288 people affected in British Columbia, 10 in Saskatchewan, 2 in Ottawa and 3 in Hamilton, one in Kitchener-Waterloo, as well as the aforementioned cases in Alberta. Many of the outbreaks have been connected to overseas travel, prompting Ontario's chief medical officer of health, Dr Arlene King, to issue a warning to be vigilant.

"In 2014, 11 cases of measles have been reported in Ontario, and all of these 11 cases were directly or indirectly associated with travel to the Philippines, Taiwan and Europe," Dr King said at a press conference on Tuesday [1 Apr 2014], according to the Globe and Mail. "Measles anywhere is a threat everywhere."

