[One upside of the stunning reemergence of measles this year [2014] in the US is increasing recognition of the disease by clinicians. As in this case, rapid recognition allows for limiting exposures in the healthcare setting, although in this case, there were "only 300" potentially exposed, still requiring a major public health response. - Mod.LM]

